---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="The House" description="A U-shaped modern home on 6 wooded acres in southwest Dayton, Ohio. Shared kitchen, central deck, seasonal pool, and a sandy fire-pit corner.">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-5 py-16">
    <p class="uppercase tracking-wider text-forest-600 text-xs font-medium">The House</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl mt-2 text-forest-900">A U-shape, wrapped around a deck.</h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-forest-800/90 leading-relaxed">
      The house is shaped like a U with the rooms running down both wings and a central deck
      in the courtyard. Behind the house is the seasonal pool. Around all of it: six acres
      of mature sycamores and black walnuts, with the neighbor's 55-acre woods extending the
      quiet in every direction.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mt-12">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-forest-100 bg-white p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest-900">Shared kitchen</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-forest-800/85">
          One full kitchen for the whole house. Coffee, cookware, fridge space, and counter room
          for meal prep — a big deal if you're here for a month or more. Bring groceries, there's
          a Kroger about 12 minutes east.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-forest-100 bg-white p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest-900">Two shared baths + the master bath</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-forest-800/85">
          One bathroom on each wing of the U-shape serves the four shared-bath rooms. The Sycamore
          master has its own private bath and walk-in closet.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-forest-100 bg-white p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest-900">Central deck</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-forest-800/85">
          The courtyard deck is the heart of the house — coffee in the morning, drinks at sunset,
          and an easy place to meet the other guests if you're staying as a group.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-forest-100 bg-white p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest-900">Seasonal pool + fire pit</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-forest-800/85">
          The pool out back is open in season, with a fire pit nearby for the evenings.
          With only five rooms on the property, it never gets crowded the way a hotel
          pool does.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-forest-100 bg-white p-6 md:col-span-2">
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest-900">The sandy corner & fire pit</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-forest-800/85">
          A natural sand deposit sits in the corner of the property — it actually feels like a
          small beach in the middle of the woods. It's the best spot for a fire and the way the
          trees frame the western sky makes for a sunset that's hard to beat.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-forest-100 bg-white p-6 md:col-span-2">
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest-900">The land</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-forest-800/85">
          Six wooded acres of sycamores and black walnuts, bordering a private 55-acre forest.
          Deer, turkeys, owls, songbirds, frogs — we've even spotted a bald eagle. You're 15
          minutes from downtown Dayton but it feels like a different state.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 rounded-3xl bg-forest-700 text-cream-50 p-8">
      <h3 class="font-display text-2xl">The host lives on the property.</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-cream-100/90">
        Alex lives in a separate detached mother-in-law suite on the property. He's around if
        you need something, but you'll rarely see him. Self check-in means you can come and go
        on your own schedule.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
